prompt: Dramatic close-up, studio photography style, focusing on an intricate antique Japanese Satsuma vase resting on a dark, textured wooden surface. In the soft-focus background, a vintage measuring caliper and an open reference book are subtly visible. Photorealistic, sharp focus on the vase, moody atmosphere, cinematic lighting, positioned slightly off-center for landscape view. --ar 16:9

prompt: Wide-angle shot capturing the interior of a well-lit, professional antiques appraiser's office or study. Sunlight streams through a large bay window on the left, illuminating dust motes in the air. Walls are lined floor-to-ceiling with bookshelves packed with leather-bound reference volumes and glass cabinets displaying various antiques (clocks, ceramics, small sculptures). An empty, polished oak partner desk sits center-right, inviting the viewer into the detailed environment. prompt: Extreme close-up, macro photography style, focusing sharply on a hallmark (e.g., a lion passant) stamped onto an antique silver spoon, being examined through a high-magnification jeweler's loupe held by meticulously clean, ungloved hands. The intricate details of the hallmark, the texture of the aged silver, and minor scratches are paramount. The background is heavily blurred (bokeh), suggesting a clean, well-lit workshop environment. Technical, bright, even lighting emphasizing detail and precision. Photorealistic, high detail, shallow depth of field. --ar 16:9

prompt: Photorealistic eye-level shot capturing a moment of interaction during an antiques appraisal consultation. An elegantly dressed senior woman with an expectant expression presents a framed, slightly faded Victorian-era portrait miniature across a polished wooden table to a calm, attentive female appraiser in modern business attire.
